"# FairUX Report

> FairUX does not provide legal judgments. Findings are UX risk signals for review.

**File:** checkout.html
**Runtime:** html
**Generated:** 2026-01-01T00:00:00.000Z
**Findings:** 3 (high: 1, medium: 1, low: 1, info: 0)

## High

### Free trial CTA lacks renewal disclosure
- **Rule:** \`subscription/free-trial-without-renewal-disclosure\`
- **Severity:** high  **Confidence:** medium
- **What:** A free-trial call to action has no nearby auto-renewal or billing-start text.
- **Why it matters:** Users may read the action as free-only and miss that billing starts automatically later.
- **Recommendation:** Place billing-start and cancellation terms next to the trial CTA.
- **Evidence:**
  - \`#start-trial\` — "Start free trial" (checkout.html:12)
- **References:** https://www.ftc.gov/business-guidance/blog

## Medium

### Pre-checked consent box
- **Rule:** \`consent/checked-checkbox\`
- **Severity:** medium  **Confidence:** high
- **What:** A consent checkbox is checked by default.
- **Why it matters:** Pre-checked boxes opt users in without an active choice.
- **Recommendation:** Leave consent boxes unchecked by default.
- **Evidence:**
  - \`#newsletter\` — "Email me offers"

## Low

### Scarcity phrasing detected
- **Rule:** \`scarcity/scarcity-phrase\`
- **Severity:** low  **Confidence:** low
- **What:** The text "Only 2 left!" may apply time/quantity pressure.
- **Why it matters:** Unverified scarcity claims can pressure users into rushed decisions.
- **Recommendation:** Show scarcity only when backed by real, current inventory data.
- **Evidence:**
  - "Only 2 left!" (checkout.html:30)
